00:23:26,969 --> 00:23:28,303
I'm not your fucking pet.

504
00:23:28,387 --> 00:23:30,639
Nah, but he liked you better
when you were a dumb animal.

505
00:23:30,722 --> 00:23:32,432
Hey, stop!

506
00:23:32,516 --> 00:23:35,185
Can you not see there is something strange
about this place?

507
00:23:35,978 --> 00:23:37,396
We need to focus.

508
00:23:37,479 --> 00:23:39,398
V1. Huh?

509
00:23:39,481 --> 00:23:42,317
[ominous music playing]

510
00:23:42,401 --> 00:23:43,819
Allons-y.

511
00:23:51,910 --> 00:23:54,621
[hip-hop music playing loudly in distance]

512
00:23:54,705 --> 00:23:56,123
[water shuts off]

513
00:23:56,206 --> 00:23:57,541
Mason!

514
00:23:59,459 --> 00:24:02,838
[Rick taking deep breaths]

515
00:24:02,921 --> 00:24:04,756
Sorry about him. He's... [sighs]

516
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:07,092
[Annie] It's okay. I used to be his age.

517
00:24:07,676 --> 00:24:09,094
I saw the sign out front.

518
00:24:09,178 --> 00:24:11,680
"In this house, we believe in Homelander"?

519
00:24:11,763 --> 00:24:14,099
New boss at the department
made everybody put 'em up.

520
00:24:14,183 --> 00:24:16,768
We answer to a Supe named Livewire now.

521
00:24:16,852 --> 00:24:19,980
I don't round up Starlighters, by the way.

522
00:24:20,063 --> 00:24:21,899
When that order comes in, I catch the flu.

523
00:24:21,982 --> 00:24:23,483
And the other deputies?

524
00:24:23,567 --> 00:24:26,403
They think that Starlighters
are coming for their kids.

525
00:24:26,486 --> 00:24:28,363
But that's a lie that Vought sells.

526
00:24:28,447 --> 00:24:31,825
-I know that.
-Then why don't you say anything?

527
00:24:31,909 --> 00:24:33,702
The last guy that spoke up disappeared,

528
00:24:33,785 --> 00:24:36,413
middle of the night,
with his wife and kids.

529
00:24:36,997 --> 00:24:41,668
I'm not proud of it, Annie,
but I have a family to protect.

530
00:24:44,504 --> 00:24:46,924
I came here to get, you know, some answers

531
00:24:47,007 --> 00:24:50,636
and some closure
before time runs out, but...

532
00:24:50,719 --> 00:24:51,970
Not what you expected?

533
00:24:53,055 --> 00:24:54,514
You could say that.

534
00:24:56,058 --> 00:24:59,019
After you left, I told myself that,

535
00:24:59,102 --> 00:25:01,021
you know, you just...
you didn't want kids,

536
00:25:01,104 --> 00:25:05,150
but maybe you just didn't want me.

537
00:25:08,111 --> 00:25:09,488
[sighs]

538
00:25:11,073 --> 00:25:12,324
Have a seat.

539
00:25:46,775 --> 00:25:48,485
This movie was shit.

540
00:25:48,568 --> 00:25:50,737
I did consider asking you
for my money back.

541
00:25:51,863 --> 00:25:54,616
I didn't always approve
of the choices you made,

542
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:56,785
but I was always proud of you.

543
00:25:58,578 --> 00:26:00,414
Maybe even more proud when you quit.

544
00:26:05,210 --> 00:26:06,545
Why did you leave?

545
00:26:08,046 --> 00:26:09,756
[sighs]

546
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:12,592
The first time I saw your mother
was on a church mission.

547
00:26:12,676 --> 00:26:14,261
El Salvador.

548
00:26:14,344 --> 00:26:17,139
We were young. [chuckles]

549
00:26:17,222 --> 00:26:18,557
Wanted to save the world.

550
00:26:20,058 --> 00:26:23,854
We were so happy when you came along.

551
00:26:24,896 --> 00:26:28,442
And your mom was dead certain
that giving you V was...

552
00:26:28,525 --> 00:26:30,027
gonna give you a better life.

553
00:26:30,110 --> 00:26:34,156
Better than a pay phone repairman
could give you.

554
00:26:34,239 --> 00:26:37,993
She asked me, "Do you know how
we can really change the world?

555
00:26:38,076 --> 00:26:39,411
Raise a superhero."

556
00:26:39,494 --> 00:26:42,289
So, you-you got on board?

557
00:26:43,373 --> 00:26:48,462
Until she started telling you
you were chosen by God.

558
00:26:49,171 --> 00:26:52,382
And th-the thing is, you believed it.

559
00:26:52,466 --> 00:26:55,510
And then she believed it, and I just...

560
00:26:56,803 --> 00:27:01,350
[sighs] I couldn't keep
lying to you, so I left.

561
00:27:01,433 --> 00:27:03,310
-You never even reached out.
-To do what?

562
00:27:03,393 --> 00:27:05,270
Shatter your dreams? Keep lying to you?

563
00:27:05,354 --> 00:27:07,314
I'd have taken either.

564
00:27:07,397 --> 00:27:09,608
I needed you.

565
00:27:14,321 --> 00:27:17,407
If I could go back
and change things, I would.

566
00:27:19,951 --> 00:27:22,079
I should have been there for you.

567
00:27:22,162 --> 00:27:23,497
Should have stood up for you.

568
00:27:25,916 --> 00:27:28,460
I'm sorry I left, Annie.

569
00:27:29,878 --> 00:27:32,339
It runs in the family, I guess.

570
00:27:33,423 --> 00:27:35,759
-What do you mean?
-I flipped out the other day,

571
00:27:35,842 --> 00:27:37,469
and I ditched someone I really love.

572
00:27:39,096 --> 00:27:41,848
It's like he's, um...
it's like he's my heart

573
00:27:41,932 --> 00:27:45,268
walking on the outside,
and if they got to him,

574
00:27:45,352 --> 00:27:46,978
-I couldn't--
-Annie.

575
00:27:47,062 --> 00:27:50,273
The people we love aren't a weakness.

576
00:27:50,357 --> 00:27:52,818
They're the reason that we fight.

577
00:28:00,492 --> 00:28:02,494
[hip-hop music playing loudly in distance]

578
00:28:02,577 --> 00:28:04,162
[sighs]

579
00:28:04,246 --> 00:28:06,081
Hey, is it all right if I talk to him?

580
00:28:06,164 --> 00:28:08,792
Of course. Uh, j-just...

581
00:28:08,875 --> 00:28:10,252
knock first.

582
00:28:11,336 --> 00:28:13,463
I learned that lesson the hard way.

583
00:28:20,554 --> 00:28:22,556
[tense, atmospheric music playing]

584
00:28:25,809 --> 00:28:27,644
Yeah. The lab is this way.

585
00:28:29,646 --> 00:28:30,981
Whoa.

586
00:28:32,065 --> 00:28:33,442
[Butcher] Fucking hell.

587
00:28:33,525 --> 00:28:35,318
They've been here a minute, haven't they?

588
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:38,447
Decades.

589
00:28:41,992 --> 00:28:43,201
Hunters.

590
00:28:43,285 --> 00:28:44,703
Look at their knives.

591
00:28:46,121 --> 00:28:48,957
These men, they killed each other.

592
00:28:49,040 --> 00:28:52,836
What if there is a monster here
but it's us?

593
00:28:52,919 --> 00:28:54,129
What the fuck are you on about, Frenchie?

594
00:28:54,212 --> 00:28:55,839
Toxoplasmosis.

595
00:28:55,922 --> 00:28:58,967
It's a parasite in cat shit.
It can infect humans.

596
00:28:59,050 --> 00:29:01,303
Makes them react with explosive anger.

597
00:29:01,386 --> 00:29:02,929
You think we ate cat shit?

598
00:29:03,013 --> 00:29:05,474
Ate? No. [stammers]

599
00:29:05,557 --> 00:29:09,352
If the V1 spilled into the groundwater,
it could mutate th-the plants.

600
00:29:09,436 --> 00:29:11,563
Their spores fills us with rage,

601
00:29:11,646 --> 00:29:14,024
we murder each other, and voilà...

602
00:29:15,025 --> 00:29:16,485
...we're plant food for these vines.

603
00:29:18,487 --> 00:29:20,447
Okay, so like
The Last of Us?

604
00:29:21,364 --> 00:29:24,159
No, that is just
The Walking Dead
with mushrooms.

605
00:29:24,784 --> 00:29:28,288
The dead campers,
the animals, these hunters.

606
00:29:28,371 --> 00:29:31,917
Surely, you all see
how strangely you've been acting.

607
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,711
Us? I've seen you blow cocaine
up your dick hole.

608
00:29:34,794 --> 00:29:37,172
[Frenchie] Wait. You have a point.

609
00:29:37,255 --> 00:29:39,466
The copious amount of drugs
I've taken for decades

610
00:29:39,549 --> 00:29:41,259
has surely altered my brain chemistry.

611
00:29:41,343 --> 00:29:43,470
That's why I'm not affected.

612
00:29:43,553 --> 00:29:45,388
Guess being a junkie
was good for something after all.

613
00:29:45,472 --> 00:29:47,349
[Mother's Milk laughs]

614
00:29:47,432 --> 00:29:49,392
Romeo and fucking Juliet.

615
00:29:49,476 --> 00:29:53,021
You two survive this war,
I give you six months, tops.

616
00:29:54,898 --> 00:29:57,359
[Butcher] Well fucking well.

617
00:30:06,701 --> 00:30:08,578
[sighs]

618
00:30:08,662 --> 00:30:10,330
Let's fucking go.

619
00:30:12,415 --> 00:30:15,252
[Frenchie]
Wh-Wh... Wh-Where are you going?

620
00:30:15,335 --> 00:30:16,711
To top those cunts.

621
00:30:16,795 --> 00:30:18,088
You'll get us killed, you fucking idiots.

622
00:30:19,172 --> 00:30:21,007
Neither of you are thinking straight.

623
00:30:21,091 --> 00:30:23,218
Get that fucking gun
out of my face, Frenchie.

624
00:30:23,301 --> 00:30:25,178
That ain't gonna do shit to me, sonny.

625
00:30:25,262 --> 00:30:26,638
No, but I will.

626
00:30:27,639 --> 00:30:30,183
Homelander and Soldier Boy kill you,
then kill us.

627
00:30:30,267 --> 00:30:33,395
Then, if there's any V1 here,
it's Homelander's.

628
00:30:34,145 --> 00:30:35,897
Does that make your family safe?

629
00:30:36,898 --> 00:30:38,358
Is that the revenge you seek?

630
00:30:39,859 --> 00:30:41,861
Does that make things right for Becca?

631
00:30:41,945 --> 00:30:43,530
[sniffles]

632
00:30:44,739 --> 00:30:45,865
Fine.

633
00:30:45,949 --> 00:30:47,576
[sighs]

634
00:30:51,204 --> 00:30:54,040
We must hurry
before we tear each other apart.

635
00:30:55,041 --> 00:30:56,626
Or the Supes do.

636
00:30:58,253 --> 00:31:00,338
So, what's the plan? God!

637
00:31:00,422 --> 00:31:02,007
-Ugh!
-The fuck, Frenchie?

638
00:31:02,090 --> 00:31:04,467
It's deer urine.
Hunters use it to attract prey,

639
00:31:04,551 --> 00:31:07,304
but we will use it
to hide our scent from Homelander.

640
00:31:07,387 --> 00:31:09,931
You spray that shit on me,
and I'll rip your fucking head off.

641
00:31:11,474 --> 00:31:14,853
I ain't counting on no goddamn deer piss
to save our asses.

642
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,399
It's just science, bro.

643
00:31:19,482 --> 00:31:22,193
When you jizz,
masculine vitality leaves your body.

644
00:31:22,277 --> 00:31:24,362
Got to hold that shit in, right, Noir?

645
00:31:25,864 --> 00:31:27,365
Right, Noir?

646
00:31:27,449 --> 00:31:29,409
[soundboard]
Fu-fu-fu-fuck you.

647
00:31:29,492 --> 00:31:31,536
Looks like you hit
the wrong button there, broseph.

648
00:31:31,620 --> 00:31:33,872
[soundboard]
B-B-Bitch says what?

649
00:31:33,955 --> 00:31:35,749
-What?
-[knocking on door]

650
00:31:35,832 --> 00:31:37,167
[Mason] What?

651
00:31:37,250 --> 00:31:39,169
[hip-hop music playing quietly]

652
00:31:41,296 --> 00:31:43,632
I just want to talk.

653
00:31:45,675 --> 00:31:48,136
-Wow.
-[Mason] Your picture was never up there.

654
00:31:48,219 --> 00:31:49,304
Yeah, good.

655
00:31:51,723 --> 00:31:55,644
Good. I mean, uh, yeah, no, that's good.

656
00:31:55,727 --> 00:31:57,020
I don't put traitors on my wall.

657
00:31:57,103 --> 00:31:58,813
Okay, you know...

658
00:31:58,897 --> 00:32:01,316
what they say about me, none of it's true.

659
00:32:01,399 --> 00:32:03,860
Do you mean the part
that you blew your way into The Seven

660
00:32:03,943 --> 00:32:06,071
or that you're a terrorist
who traffics children?

661
00:32:06,154 --> 00:32:09,491
So that's, like, a hard no
on getting into the back of my van?

662
00:32:10,825 --> 00:32:13,953
Hey, look, Mason,

663
00:32:14,037 --> 00:32:16,247
you go to school at Homelander Academy

664
00:32:16,331 --> 00:32:20,335
and you come home and you watch
thousands of TikToks every day.

665
00:32:20,418 --> 00:32:22,796
How is the truth
supposed to compete with that?

666
00:32:23,380 --> 00:32:24,589
Whatever.

667
00:32:24,673 --> 00:32:26,591
You're, like, the FBI's Most Wanted.

668
00:32:26,675 --> 00:32:30,261
Oh, okay. Well, like it or not,
the FBI's Most Wanted is your sister,

669
00:32:30,345 --> 00:32:34,599
so you can keep being an asshole about it
or, you know, we can also talk about it.

670
00:32:34,683 --> 00:32:36,476
Is there a third option?

671
00:32:41,314 --> 00:32:42,607
[Annie] Let me guess.

672
00:32:42,691 --> 00:32:46,861
Chocolate cream-filled
every Thursday morning, right?

673
00:32:47,779 --> 00:32:49,531
Dad used to take me before school.

674
00:32:51,074 --> 00:32:53,576
[sighs] It's one of the things
I miss the most, actually.

675
00:32:54,452 --> 00:32:57,539
I think he was just taking me
as his beard.

676
00:32:59,374 --> 00:33:01,793
Yeah, I feel like he's giving me diabetes.

677
00:33:01,876 --> 00:33:03,586
[laughs softly]

678
00:33:05,588 --> 00:33:07,966
[tense, atmospheric music playing]

679
00:33:14,055 --> 00:33:16,057
[wind howling]

680
00:33:24,482 --> 00:33:26,276
[Frenchie] Okay, it's not here.

681
00:33:26,359 --> 00:33:28,653
Fuck this and fuck you and fuck me.

682
00:33:28,737 --> 00:33:30,488
This is a goddam waste of time.

683
00:33:34,826 --> 00:33:35,910
[Mother's Milk] Butcher.

684
00:33:36,995 --> 00:33:38,538
Take a look.

685
00:33:38,621 --> 00:33:40,915
Maybe some motherfucker beat us to it.

686
00:33:40,999 --> 00:33:43,042
Not too long ago, neither.

687
00:33:43,126 --> 00:33:45,754
They punched 80 years of rust
right off the safe.

688
00:33:46,838 --> 00:33:49,674
Now, how many Supes do we know
that can punch this hard?

689
00:33:49,758 --> 00:33:51,384
A dozen. Maybe more.

690
00:33:52,886 --> 00:33:54,012
[Kimiko] What is it?

691
00:33:55,555 --> 00:33:57,432
-Heroin.
-[Kimiko] Heroin.

692
00:33:57,515 --> 00:33:59,893
-Of course you would fucking know that.
-[Hughie laughs]

693
00:34:02,020 --> 00:34:03,646
Huh. So...

694
00:34:03,730 --> 00:34:06,024
a punch like a bleeding sledgehammer

695
00:34:06,107 --> 00:34:08,359
and a taste for fucking smack.

696
00:34:09,819 --> 00:34:11,029
Bombsight.

697
00:34:11,112 --> 00:34:14,073
[Frenchie] No one has seen
Bombsight for decades.

698
00:34:14,157 --> 00:34:15,492
He's likely dead.

699
00:34:15,575 --> 00:34:16,910
What if he's not, asshole?

700
00:34:17,535 --> 00:34:20,455
He'd be about the only other cunt
that would know this shit was here.

701
00:34:20,538 --> 00:34:22,999
[Hughie] You mean Bombsight
from Soldier Boy's first team?

702
00:34:23,082 --> 00:34:25,543
Wouldn't he have already been
shot up with V1? What's he need more for?

703
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:32,926
[Rick] Hey, Ed.

704
00:34:33,009 --> 00:34:34,511
-Everything all right?
-[Ed] Yeah,

705
00:34:34,594 --> 00:34:36,513
I'm sorry to bother you on your day off.

706
00:34:36,596 --> 00:34:39,849
This is gonna sound crazy.
Is Starlight in there?

707
00:34:39,933 --> 00:34:41,351
I'm s... I'm sorry, what?

708
00:34:41,434 --> 00:34:42,685
I got a call from Mason.

709
00:34:44,020 --> 00:34:45,939
But it's a joke, right?

710
00:34:46,022 --> 00:34:47,565
Tell me it's a joke.

711
00:34:47,649 --> 00:34:49,651
[quiet, tense music playing]

712
00:34:54,447 --> 00:34:55,657
She's my daughter.

713
00:34:55,740 --> 00:34:56,866
Your daughter?

714
00:34:56,950 --> 00:34:59,285
[whispers] Jesus Christ.
Can't he ever fucking lie?

715
00:34:59,369 --> 00:35:01,538
I've known you 20 years, and y-you never--

716
00:35:01,621 --> 00:35:03,581
-I should have told you.
-She's a serial killer.

717
00:35:03,665 --> 00:35:06,376
She's not. I promise you.

718
00:35:07,085 --> 00:35:11,047
I'm begging you,
get back in your cruiser and let this go.

719
00:35:11,130 --> 00:35:14,801
Are you crazy?
I am not dying in a prison camp over this.

720
00:35:14,884 --> 00:35:16,094
I got to take her in.

721
00:35:17,554 --> 00:35:19,472
You need to step aside right now.

722
00:35:19,556 --> 00:35:21,432
Please, Ed, just take a breath.

723
00:35:21,516 --> 00:35:23,101
[trembling breaths]

724
00:35:23,893 --> 00:35:25,687
-Hands up right now.
-[Annie] I don't think so.

725
00:35:25,770 --> 00:35:26,896
Walk away.

726
00:35:26,980 --> 00:35:29,107
-[whirring]
-[electrical buzzing]

727
00:35:29,190 --> 00:35:31,150
-Ed, put it down.
-I said now.

728
00:35:31,234 --> 00:35:32,777
-Walk away.
-[Ed] No.

729
00:35:32,861 --> 00:35:34,696
-You're under arrest.
-[Rick] Ed, relax.

730
00:35:34,779 --> 00:35:35,989
-Everybody, please, just--
-[Ed] I'm warning you.

731
00:35:36,072 --> 00:35:37,490
I said walk away.

732
00:35:37,574 --> 00:35:39,909
Would the both of you fucking stop!

733
00:35:41,286 --> 00:35:43,037
[whirring and electrical buzzing fade]

734
00:35:45,415 --> 00:35:47,166
I-I'm sorry, I just...

735
00:35:47,250 --> 00:35:49,961
Ed, we sit next to each other
in church every Sunday.

736
00:35:50,044 --> 00:35:53,464
After Pam died, you ate dinner here
for how many months?

737
00:35:53,548 --> 00:35:55,383
Yeah, and you lied to my face
the whole time.

738
00:35:55,466 --> 00:35:57,218
[Rick] I know you're scared.
I'm scared, too.

739
00:35:57,302 --> 00:35:58,928
But what Vought's been making us do,

740
00:35:59,012 --> 00:36:01,764
pulling people out of their homes,
our neighbors,

741
00:36:01,848 --> 00:36:03,182
and sending them to...

742
00:36:04,183 --> 00:36:05,560
God knows where.

743
00:36:05,643 --> 00:36:06,895
You know it's wrong.

744
00:36:10,231 --> 00:36:12,442
Annie's my daughter, and I love her.

745
00:36:12,525 --> 00:36:14,485
I should've stood up for her
a long time ago.

746
00:36:15,278 --> 00:36:16,696
She's not what they say she is.

747
00:36:16,779 --> 00:36:18,531
She's a good person, Ed.

748
00:36:18,615 --> 00:36:20,825
And if good people stop trying
to do the right thing,

749
00:36:20,909 --> 00:36:23,453
then what the hell chance do we have?

750
00:36:28,833 --> 00:36:30,460
She better be gone in an hour,

751
00:36:30,543 --> 00:36:33,880
or I swear to God,
I'm coming back with Livewire,

752
00:36:33,963 --> 00:36:36,049
I'm hauling you both in.

753
00:36:36,132 --> 00:36:38,426
