00:52:11,775 --> 00:52:13,277
[Kathy] It definitely wasn't,

1012
00:52:13,360 --> 00:52:15,863
-but that's kind of you.
-[chuckles]

1013
00:52:18,240 --> 00:52:20,534
You have something you want to say?

1014
00:52:20,617 --> 00:52:21,827
Sorry.

1015
00:52:23,328 --> 00:52:24,663
You want to try that again?

1016
00:52:25,747 --> 00:52:27,165
[sighs] I'm sorry.

1017
00:52:27,249 --> 00:52:29,543
[Rick] Good.
But you're grounded till you're 20.

1018
00:52:29,626 --> 00:52:31,503
Mm, more like 30.

1019
00:52:32,588 --> 00:52:34,882
I hope we see each other again.

1020
00:52:35,966 --> 00:52:37,217
Me, too.

1021
00:52:44,474 --> 00:52:45,767
[Rick] Annie?

1022
00:52:45,851 --> 00:52:47,686
Don't make the same mistake I did.

1023
00:52:48,770 --> 00:52:51,690
Don't give up on the people you love,
all right?

1024
00:52:51,773 --> 00:52:53,442
[wistful music playing]

1025
00:52:53,525 --> 00:52:54,526
[chuckles softly]

1026
00:52:58,113 --> 00:52:59,531
[clears throat]

1027
00:53:09,374 --> 00:53:10,667
[sighs]

1028
00:53:13,170 --> 00:53:15,172
[gasping breaths]

1029
00:53:20,344 --> 00:53:22,346
[heavy thudding]

1030
00:53:28,101 --> 00:53:30,604
[tense, atmospheric music playing]

1031
00:53:31,688 --> 00:53:34,274
[groaning]

1032
00:53:38,862 --> 00:53:41,239
[breathing heavily]

1033
00:53:44,451 --> 00:53:46,119
[shouts]

1034
00:53:55,796 --> 00:53:57,798
[whirring]

1035
00:54:05,097 --> 00:54:06,848
The V1 wasn't here.

1036
00:54:15,023 --> 00:54:16,441
Were you...

1037
00:54:18,151 --> 00:54:19,277
Were you crying?

1038
00:54:22,906 --> 00:54:25,075
Just fucking do it already.

1039
00:54:25,826 --> 00:54:28,412
[somber music playing]

1040
00:54:46,179 --> 00:54:47,514
[gasps softly]

1041
00:54:51,143 --> 00:54:52,394
[door closes]

1042
00:54:58,608 --> 00:54:59,943
Thank you.

1043
00:55:00,736 --> 00:55:02,988
We wouldn't have made it out
if you hadn't stepped up.

1044
00:55:04,072 --> 00:55:07,534
Oh. Yeah, well, taking charge...

1045
00:55:08,785 --> 00:55:10,704
...was the most horrible thing
I've ever done.

1046
00:55:10,787 --> 00:55:13,165
Never let me do it again. Never.

1047
00:55:17,377 --> 00:55:19,629
I'm sorry I called you
a feckless junkie man-whore.

1048
00:55:20,714 --> 00:55:23,592
I don't remember you calling me that.

1049
00:55:23,675 --> 00:55:26,261
I didn't? I thought I did.

1050
00:55:27,345 --> 00:55:29,014
You're not wrong.

1051
00:55:29,097 --> 00:55:32,517
I was, once.

1052
00:55:32,601 --> 00:55:34,728
But I am clean now.

1053
00:55:34,811 --> 00:55:38,148
And I can be whatever you need.

1054
00:55:39,149 --> 00:55:41,777
[soft, atmospheric music playing]

1055
00:55:43,653 --> 00:55:45,489
I don't want to change you.

1056
00:55:46,907 --> 00:55:49,159
It's that...

1057
00:55:50,869 --> 00:55:53,205
...I'm trying to change myself.

1058
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:56,833
The reason I can speak now, it's...

1059
00:55:56,917 --> 00:55:59,961
it's because I did so much work
to let go of my...

1060
00:56:00,045 --> 00:56:01,546
chaos.

1061
00:56:03,173 --> 00:56:04,341
The thing is...

1062
00:56:05,425 --> 00:56:06,843
...you love chaos.

1063
00:56:06,927 --> 00:56:08,345
You thrive in it.

1064
00:56:08,428 --> 00:56:09,638
Which is fine, but...

1065
00:56:11,223 --> 00:56:13,141
...I can't go back to that.

1066
00:56:18,021 --> 00:56:20,065
So, where does that leave us?

1067
00:56:29,658 --> 00:56:30,992
[groans]

1068
00:56:31,076 --> 00:56:32,953
-[whirring]
-[electrical buzzing]

1069
00:56:33,036 --> 00:56:34,204
[loud thud]

1070
00:56:48,426 --> 00:56:49,886
I'm sorry.

1071
00:56:49,970 --> 00:56:51,596
I shouldn't have left you.
I should've been here.

1072
00:56:51,680 --> 00:56:55,100
Actually, I'm so, so glad you weren't.

1073
00:56:55,183 --> 00:56:56,351
Super good day to miss.

1074
00:56:59,312 --> 00:57:01,606
-[speaks Russian over video]
-[device clicking over video]

1075
00:57:01,690 --> 00:57:03,692
[clears throat over video]

1076
00:57:03,775 --> 00:57:05,777
[Russian chatter continues over video]

1077
00:57:10,991 --> 00:57:12,117
[Butcher] Listen, mate.

1078
00:57:12,701 --> 00:57:14,911
-That shite I said...
-Hey.

1079
00:57:14,995 --> 00:57:16,663
Don't tell me you didn't mean it, a'ight?

1080
00:57:16,746 --> 00:57:19,583
'Cause I sure as hell meant
every fucking word I said.

1081
00:57:19,666 --> 00:57:21,293
So, we got a problem?

1082
00:57:26,256 --> 00:57:27,841
[chuckles]

1083
00:57:27,924 --> 00:57:29,050
We cool, man.

1084
00:57:29,134 --> 00:57:30,468
We cool.

1085
00:57:38,101 --> 00:57:39,477
What are you doing?

1086
00:57:39,561 --> 00:57:41,021
Just thinking.

1087
00:57:41,104 --> 00:57:44,357
Well, the shit show is on.

1088
00:57:44,441 --> 00:57:45,442
[button clicks]

1089
00:57:45,525 --> 00:57:47,485
[singer over video] ♪
From sea
♪

1090
00:57:47,569 --> 00:57:51,531
♪
to shining
♪

1091
00:57:51,615 --> 00:57:54,451
[full choir] ♪
sea
♪

1092
00:57:54,534 --> 00:57:58,163
♪
America
♪♪

1093
00:57:58,246 --> 00:58:01,249
-[cheering and applause]
-Yes! Yes!

1094
00:58:05,545 --> 00:58:07,005
Brothers and sisters.

1095
00:58:07,088 --> 00:58:08,798
[cheering]

1096
00:58:08,882 --> 00:58:12,260
Brothers and sisters,
we are truly, truly fortunate

1097
00:58:12,344 --> 00:58:14,137
to bear witness on this day.

1098
00:58:14,221 --> 00:58:17,057
-[congregation murmuring]
-Because today...

1099
00:58:17,140 --> 00:58:19,893
is the greatest day
in the history of Samaritan's Embrace.

1100
00:58:19,976 --> 00:58:22,479
-Can I get an amen?
-[congregation] Amen!

1101
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,982
I mean, I love all this, love,

1102
00:58:26,066 --> 00:58:28,360
but don't you believe in Jesus
or whatever?

1103
00:58:28,443 --> 00:58:30,195
I did.

1104
00:58:30,278 --> 00:58:31,613
Now I believe in Homelander.

1105
00:58:31,696 --> 00:58:33,365
-[Bashley]
She's lying.
-No shit.

1106
00:58:33,448 --> 00:58:35,492
-Excuse me?
-[laughs softly]

1107
00:58:35,575 --> 00:58:37,118
[congregation murmuring]

1108
00:58:37,202 --> 00:58:39,996
But today, brothers and sisters, today,

1109
00:58:40,080 --> 00:58:43,208
we set America back on its true course.

1110
00:58:43,291 --> 00:58:44,876
[cheering and applause]

1111
00:58:44,960 --> 00:58:47,128
Starting today, brothers and sisters,

1112
00:58:47,212 --> 00:58:52,634
we commit ourselves
to a divine rebranding.

1113
00:58:52,717 --> 00:58:56,471
We will be patriots of faith.

1114
00:58:56,554 --> 00:59:00,558
We will fulfill
our Founding Fathers' dream.

1115
00:59:00,642 --> 00:59:05,522
Today, starting today,
Samaritan's Embrace becomes

1116
00:59:05,605 --> 00:59:08,858
the Democratic Church of America.

1117
00:59:08,942 --> 00:59:11,778
[cheering and applause]

1118
00:59:12,988 --> 00:59:16,992
And here, to share his holy plan
for our new church,

1119
00:59:17,075 --> 00:59:18,952
he is not just a man...

1120
00:59:19,035 --> 00:59:21,121
[congregation murmuring]

1121
00:59:21,204 --> 00:59:24,624
...he's not just a super man...

1122
00:59:28,920 --> 00:59:34,175
...he is the Prophet of the Lord!

1123
00:59:34,259 --> 00:59:36,136
[applause]

1124
00:59:36,219 --> 00:59:40,140
He is the Prophet of America!

1125
00:59:40,223 --> 00:59:43,977
He is the Prophet Homelander!

1126
00:59:45,645 --> 00:59:48,189
[cheering]

1127
01:00:01,036 --> 01:00:04,414
[congregation chanting] Homelander!
Homelander! Homelander!

1128
01:00:04,497 --> 01:00:06,291
Homelander! Home--

1129
01:00:11,338 --> 01:00:12,505
[gasps]

1130
01:00:14,424 --> 01:00:18,011
[church organ playing
"America the Beautiful"]

1131
01:00:44,079 --> 01:00:46,081
♪ ♪

1132
01:01:14,109 --> 01:01:16,111
♪ ♪

1133
01:01:38,133 --> 01:01:40,135
♪ ♪

1134
01:02:06,286 --> 01:02:08,288
♪ ♪
